('Au Coeur Caraïbe St Barth', 'Saint-Barthelemy', 20, 'Quality services, calm, resting and peaceful. Comfortable bedroom. King size bed, air conditioned, bathroom, small kitchen all equipped, flat screen, DVD, Wi-Fi, big patio, 2 exotics swimming pool, private parking, exceptional sea view.', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d3796.518371796331!2d-62.80968278502806!3d17.907960487768577!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x8c0ddfe93fa2ac03%3A0x44d6325f3574d325!2sAu+Coeur+Caraibe+St+Barth!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1490275066150" frameborder="0" style="" allowfullscreen></iframe>', '<div id="TA_cdsratingsonlywide217" class="TA_cdsratingsonlywide">\r\n<ul id="nSdATf" class="TA_links jBdD9Gjz">\r\n<li id="pX5VC7ZohDN" class="FS0VXdh">\r\n<a target="_blank" href="https://www.tripadvisor.com/"><img src="https://www.tripadvisor.com/img/cdsi/img2/branding/tripadvisor_logo_transp_340x80-18034-2.png" alt="TripAdvisor"/></a>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<script src="https://www.jscache.com/wejs?wtype=cdsratingsonlywide&amp;uniq=217&amp;locationId=8714831&amp;lang=en_US&amp;border=true&amp;shadow=true&amp;display_version=2"></script>'),
('Bonne Nuit Paris', 'Paris', 50, 'Built in 1609, under the reign of Henry IV, on a ground sold by the Grand Prayer of the Temple, the Archduke of Angouleme, then transform after the Revolution into a small 5 floors building, our establishment will welcome you for your stay in “The city of Lights”.<br />\r\nLocated in the historical neighbourhood of the Marais, you can go for a walk to discover many private hotels and its cultural places, stroll in shopping areas and art gallery, and hanging out in outdoor pubs or restaurants tables.<br />\r\nYou wish to enjoy a full stay in discoveries and emotions, so don’t hesitate and come discover our guesthouse in Montmartre.', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d2624.7085664892875!2d2.3613292157356165!3d48.863767479288086!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x47e66e065deacba5%3A0xadd230e6fa51bb11!2sBonne+Nuit+Paris!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1488278648021" frameborder="0" style="" allowfullscreen></iframe>', '<div id="TA_cdsratingsonlywide754" class="TA_cdsratingsonlywide">\r\n<ul id="CzoDWVTzNTVX" class="TA_links AT7F8cgS43r">\r\n<li id="KrhJXngB" class="eKjYOoN0Dn">\r\n<a target="_blank" href="https://www.tripadvisor.com/"><img src="https://www.tripadvisor.com/img/cdsi/img2/branding/tripadvisor_logo_transp_340x80-18034-2.png" alt="TripAdvisor"/></a>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<script src="https://www.jscache.com/wejs?wtype=cdsratingsonlywide&amp;uniq=754&amp;locationId=1012229&amp;lang=en_US&amp;border=true&amp;shadow=true&amp;display_version=2"></script>'),
('Casa del Sole', 'Corse', 25, 'There are places where we don’t come accidently. There are hidden and unsuspected places that are peaceful, calm and warm and preciously discreet, breath this atmosphere like island, this feeling of the end of the world and lost paradise.\r\nAround the beautiful golf of Favone, La Casa del Sol is in the heart of sublime landscape, while close to Solenzara and at tens kilometres of Porto-Vecchio or even Bonifacio.', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d2975.2998640325427!2d9.394189015507148!3d41.77875077923018!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x12d992246a8c453d%3A0xf29017ca0c2fd330!2sVilla+Casa+Del+Sole!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1488278819873" frameborder="0" style="" allowfullscreen></iframe>', ''),
('Casa Sarrinca', 'Corse', 20, 'In south Corse, on the Lords land, Serra di Scopamena is the highest of Alta Rocca, at 900 meters’ altitude. Here was born the guesthouse Casa Sarrinca, owned by Francine, originally from Valinco and by Catherine, originally from Serra, birthplace of her maternal family.<br />\r\nYou are in the heart of a pleasant village of mountain, but you’ll forget sooner because the house has an impressing view on the valley Rizzanese and calm.<br />\r\nCasa Sarrinca is an ancient granite house all renewed; ideally situated in the middle of Serra di Sacopamena, behind the church beach.<br />\r\nEverything was thought faithfully to make us want to stay: the colours, the fabrics, the objects were well chosen to preserve the harmony of this place.', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d2976.5143982228283!2d9.096970315506367!3d41.75256597923238!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x12da25d5d0597219%3A0xad780b93d99a40a9!2sCASA+SARRINCA!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1488278933641" frameborder="0" style="" allowfullscreen></iframe>', '<div id="TA_cdsratingsonlywide94" class="TA_cdsratingsonlywide">\r\n<ul id="Cp1kcfv" class="TA_links WN3cLlIrzetM">\r\n<li id="CZiqwSc" class="kQnkR6kORuWH">\r\n<a target="_blank" href="https://www.tripadvisor.com/"><img src="https://www.tripadvisor.com/img/cdsi/img2/branding/tripadvisor_logo_transp_340x80-18034-2.png" alt="TripAdvisor"/></a>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<script src="https://www.jscache.com/wejs?wtype=cdsratingsonlywide&amp;uniq=94&amp;locationId=7987035&amp;lang=en_US&amp;border=true&amp;shadow=true&amp;display_version=2"></script>\r\n'),
('Château de Riverie', 'Lyon', 10, 'Construit au XIème siècle dans les Monts du Lyonnais, le château de Riverie domine l’agglomération lyonnaise \r\net offre un panorama sur le Pilat, la Vallée du Rhône et la chaîne des Alpes.<br />\r\nSituée au cœur du village médiéval très calme où de nombreuses ruelles convergent vers le chemin de ronde, notre maison d''hotes de charme vous attend pour un séjour touristique, une étape lors d’un déplacement privé ou professionnel.', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d2791.56255115253!2d4.586269315626898!3d45.599337979102735!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x47f4f95f5a748d71%3A0x981f19cdacbc3b0e!2sChambres+et+Table+d&#39;H%C3%B4tes+Riverie+69+-+Rh%C3%B4ne+Alpes+-+Ch%C3%A2teau+de+Riverie!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1490282733837" frameborder="0" style="" allowfullscreen></iframe>', '<div id="TA_cdsratingsonlywide18" class="TA_cdsratingsonlywide">\r\n<ul id="kBXYaZHM6U" class="TA_links ocSinM">\r\n<li id="NDnC25Z" class="QmiJLqW">\r\n<a target="_blank" href="https://www.tripadvisor.com/"><img src="https://www.tripadvisor.com/img/cdsi/img2/branding/tripadvisor_logo_transp_340x80-18034-2.png" alt="TripAdvisor"/></a>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<script src="https://www.jscache.com/wejs?wtype=cdsratingsonlywide&amp;uniq=18&amp;locationId=7060304&amp;lang=en_US&amp;border=true&amp;shadow=true&amp;display_version=2"></script>'),
('Château des Salles', 'Bordeaux', 20, 'You will receive a warm and smiling welcome to this friendly and elegant family home from your charming hostess, Sylvie Couillaud.<br />\r\nYou may visit the Bordeaux and Cognac vineyards, choose to spend a day by the beach or discover the Romanesque churches before coming back to enjoy « La vie de Château ».', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d2797.8847908536695!2d-0.7129441843772482!3d45.4721246791011!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x4801ae439c539503%3A0xff29cef767842b97!2sCh%C3%A2teau+Des+Salles!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1490280895923"  frameborder="0" style="" allowfullscreen></iframe>', '<div id="TA_cdsratingsonlywide207" class="TA_cdsratingsonlywide">\r\n<ul id="uVxu8grjLXrh" class="TA_links HcBrFphs">\r\n<li id="q2EBLs8j1" class="NlVjNCaXW">\r\n<a target="_blank" href="https://www.tripadvisor.com/"><img src="https://www.tripadvisor.com/img/cdsi/img2/branding/tripadvisor_logo_transp_340x80-18034-2.png" alt="TripAdvisor"/></a>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<script src="https://www.jscache.com/wejs?wtype=cdsratingsonlywide&amp;uniq=207&amp;locationId=325297&amp;lang=en_US&amp;border=true&amp;shadow=true&amp;display_version=2"></script>'),
('Château Eza', 'French Riviera', 20, 'Of all the hotels on the Cote d''Azur, Château Eza is the most stunning, with its Gourmet Restaurant, tucked away in Eze in one of the most enchanting locations on the Côte d''Azur. The 14 intimate rooms and suites of this 400-year- old Chateau, also a former residence to a Swedish Prince, offer epic vistas over the Cote d''Azur, often from private balconies and terraces, as does Chateau Eza''s Gourmet restaurant, itself overlooking the sun-kissed horizons of the FRENCH RIVIERA.<br />\r\nExquisite and intimate, the 14 rooms and suites château clings to the side of the ancient rock walls of Eze, a thousand-year- old medieval village more than 400 meters above the Mediterranean Sea. The hotel Chateau Eza offers 14 luxurious rooms and suites, each of them uniquely designed in the tradition of the castle.', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d2883.176801952261!2d7.3587799155671965!3d43.72765387911876!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x12cdc36617d44f31%3A0xb9256013b19ae7d8!2sCh%C3%A2teau+Eza!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1488379495531" frameborder="0" style="" allowfullscreen></iframe>', '<div id="TA_cdsratingsonlywide827" class="TA_cdsratingsonlywide">\r\n<ul id="f5HKkJv" class="TA_links kIJr6oC">\r\n<li id="0mMYAZ" class="ZS5bhoARi">\r\n<a target="_blank" href="https://www.tripadvisor.com/"><img src="https://www.tripadvisor.com/img/cdsi/img2/branding/tripadvisor_logo_transp_340x80-18034-2.png" alt="TripAdvisor"/></a>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<script src="https://www.jscache.com/wejs?wtype=cdsratingsonlywide&amp;uniq=827&amp;locationId=233655&amp;lang=en_US&amp;border=true&amp;shadow=true&amp;display_version=2"></script>\r\n'),
('Château Meyre', 'Bordeaux', 15, 'Located in the heart of Medoc, right next to the famous Margaux vineyards, Château Meyre has been growing vines for more than three centuries.<br />\r\nOur estate is listed among the very finest wineries in Medoc since 1876.<br />\r\nWe cover 17 hectares of the best plots of land in Avensan. In 1992, the domain was expanded to the Margaux area through a 2 hectares acquisition of wines.<br />\r\nSince 2011 we’ve been labialised organic wine. Our organic wines and vineyard are complimented by our organic surroundings.<br />\r\nOur “Terroir” has accomplished the authenticity and success of our organic wine.', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d2819.833186769578!2d-0.7690601843915362!3d45.02831167909815!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x4801d8311a03b7af%3A0x2a1586302fd44b99!2sChateau+Meyre!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1490282259626" frameborder="0" style="" allowfullscreen></iframe>', '<div id="TA_cdsratingsonlywide838" class="TA_cdsratingsonlywide">\r\n<ul id="LqzcksSQy" class="TA_links wWbPAMJAVUyA">\r\n<li id="9WWEBix2k8" class="qdSem8STyGG">\r\n<a target="_blank" href="https://www.tripadvisor.com/"><img src="https://www.tripadvisor.com/img/cdsi/img2/branding/tripadvisor_logo_transp_340x80-18034-2.png" alt="TripAdvisor"/></a>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<script src="https://www.jscache.com/wejs?wtype=cdsratingsonlywide&amp;uniq=838&amp;locationId=589012&amp;lang=en_US&amp;border=true&amp;shadow=true&amp;display_version=2"></script>'),
('Demeure des Sacres', 'Reims', 12, 'Near the gates of the Cathedral, the private hotel located at 29 rue Libergier was built end of 19th century and the lounge in the art-déco style (reconstruction of Reims after World War I).<br />\r\nRecently restored as a luxury guest house called “La Demeure des Sacres”, it is an exceptional site.<br />\r\nWith around 500 sq m of liveable space, ceilings over 3.30 meters high (11 feet) and its large 450 sq m garden, it brings calm and comfort right in the city centre.<br />\r\nThis guest house of character offers four bedrooms (including two suites). You will be warmly welcomed by our family.<br />\r\nAn art-déco guest lounge is available for resting, reading or enjoying a home-made snack or brunch, together with a glass of champagne.', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d2604.2922444674455!2d4.027634115748907!3d49.25190647932804!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x47e97454800bf539%3A0x902e865f8f33259b!2sLa+Demeure+des+Sacres!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1490284149385" frameborder="0" style="" allowfullscreen></iframe>', '<div id="TA_cdsratingsonlywide537" class="TA_cdsratingsonlywide">\r\n<ul id="If4Cj5lbqQ5b" class="TA_links mYSylk1rHd">\r\n<li id="N4tAxm" class="wxjzCVptL85">\r\n<a target="_blank" href="https://www.tripadvisor.com/"><img src="https://www.tripadvisor.com/img/cdsi/img2/branding/tripadvisor_logo_transp_340x80-18034-2.png" alt="TripAdvisor"/></a>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<script src="https://www.jscache.com/wejs?wtype=cdsratingsonlywide&amp;uniq=537&amp;locationId=4372138&amp;lang=en_US&amp;border=true&amp;shadow=true&amp;display_version=2"></script>'),
('Demeure M', 'Strasbourg', 20, 'Pavilion located in Strasbourg, ideal for family stay, between friends, or for business travel.<br />\r\nCome cover an incredible range of activity as you desire.<br />\r\nEither you are looking for a comfy, a high-class comfort zone or a romantic escapade, an excursion to relax, to taste local specialities or to simply visit Strasbourg, there is something for everyone.<br />\r\nStart off your day gently with breakfast of the clubhouse and let yourself transported to an extraordinary trip of flavours in gourmet restaurant at the residence;<br />\r\nFor the most tense and anxious ones, nothing is better than a small relaxation at the Spa M du Pavilion for a nice resting and relax moment.<br />\r\nAt the M residence, your desires will be fulfilled.', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d2639.068592869895!2d7.739056515726244!3d48.58938547926207!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x4796c848a2052921%3A0xbe6503dd4fbb45ce!2sDemeure+M+%7C+Maison+d&#39;H%C3%B4tes+Strasbourg!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1488279003589" frameborder="0" style="" allowfullscreen></iframe>', '<div id="TA_cdsratingsonlywide822" class="TA_cdsratingsonlywide">\r\n<ul id="Zt7INC" class="TA_links jl2mzjeol0Ng">\r\n<li id="pxTcU1u2" class="5mouItc4Vl">\r\n<a target="_blank" href="https://www.tripadvisor.com/"><img src="https://www.tripadvisor.com/img/cdsi/img2/branding/tripadvisor_logo_transp_340x80-18034-2.png" alt="TripAdvisor"/></a>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<script src="https://www.jscache.com/wejs?wtype=cdsratingsonlywide&amp;uniq=822&amp;locationId=10403825&amp;lang=en_US&amp;border=true&amp;shadow=true&amp;display_version=2"></script>'),
('Domaine des Saints Pères', 'Haute-Savoie', 10, 'A 19th century mansion in the heart of the Savoyard countryside, just 10 minutes from Chambéry, Les Saints Pères is turning hospitality into an art form. A certain lifestyle, a special way of taking care of guests… welcome to this unique and unusual establishment! If you are looking for a charming, comfortable residence that good taste and refinement has transformed into a hotel... just follow the guide.<br />\r\nIf you are looking for a gift, or simply want to treat yourself, we have gift boxes available : a stay at the Domaine des Saints Pères or an unforgettable romantic dinner...', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d2794.729530496692!2d5.908150115624827!3d45.53564807910191!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x478ba99d99c096f7%3A0x30e9163348c4b55!2sDomaine+des+Saints+P%C3%A8res!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1490284673367" frameborder="0" style="" allowfullscreen></iframe>', ''),
('Domaine du Chalet', 'Reims', 17, 'Built in 1860 and completed in 1864, Le Chalet, used to be Madame POMMERY''s residence. She was the creator of this prestigious Champagne and is at the origin of the village name.<br />\r\nIn 1902, the president Emile LOUBET, after a visit at Le Chalet, discovered Madame POMMERY''s passion for roses and in the bulletin for official announcements, a presidential revue was issued : Chigny became Chigny les Roses.<br />\r\nThis great house combines an elegant architecture and a savoury rustic charm as its name indicates. It covery the top of the hillside. <br />\r\nAt breakfast time, invitation to travel... in the middle of the Champagne vineyards in this wonderful cuisine that reveals some very pretty views or escape the time of a reading by the fire of the lounge woodwork field Chalet invite you to spend pleasant moments of relaxation and enjoyment...', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d2609.4169611480897!2d4.0563586157455465!3d49.15469337931766!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x47e9718a8aa13463%3A0x24cdb0c52ca3b446!2sDomaine+du+Chalet!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1490283950979" frameborder="0" style="" allowfullscreen></iframe>', '<div id="TA_cdsratingsonlywide616" class="TA_cdsratingsonlywide">\r\n<ul id="jTaYHiU" class="TA_links KIkVShM">\r\n<li id="cuK0zN2" class="G6EX76To">\r\n<a target="_blank" href="https://www.tripadvisor.com/"><img src="https://www.tripadvisor.com/img/cdsi/img2/branding/tripadvisor_logo_transp_340x80-18034-2.png" alt="TripAdvisor"/></a>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<script src="https://www.jscache.com/wejs?wtype=cdsratingsonlywide&amp;uniq=616&amp;locationId=4808576&amp;lang=en_US&amp;border=true&amp;shadow=true&amp;display_version=2"></script>'),
('Fare Pea Iti', 'French Polynesia', 20, 'A few minutes with the private boat of Fare Pea Iti Lodge from the airport of its sister Raiatea island, Taha''a looks like a huge colorful and fragrant garden where vanilla, precious orchid reigns princess. This is indeed Taha''a that occurred more than 80% of the famous Tahitian vanilla, the favorite variety of true connoisseurs. Planters willingly introduce visitors to the complex rituals of this spice, which you can inhale the sweet fragrance and captivating in every corner of the island. An island with authentic charm: Time seems to have stopped at Taha''a, secret and wild island that looks like a large, lush garden. The houses blend into this dream and just walk along Ferry paths to discover exuberant flora and largely preserved.<br />\r\nAn island with authentic charm: Time seems to have stopped at Taha''a, secret and wild island that looks like a large, lush garden. The houses blend into this dream and just walk along Ferry paths to discover exuberant flora and largely preserved.', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d3823.909769461422!2d-151.48858048504576!3d-16.581048888566535!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x76bd8367309580e7%3A0x4aecf67ae312c371!2sFare+Pea+Iti!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1490267507534" frameborder="0" style="" allowfullscreen></iframe>', '<div id="TA_cdsratingsonlywide439" class="TA_cdsratingsonlywide">\r\n<ul id="y03zWxOxyB" class="TA_links vCjazBblvS">\r\n<li id="P4EhovDsyik" class="DIswumNYiyel">\r\n<a target="_blank" href="https://www.tripadvisor.com/"><img src="https://www.tripadvisor.com/img/cdsi/img2/branding/tripadvisor_logo_transp_340x80-18034-2.png" alt="TripAdvisor"/></a>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<script src="https://www.jscache.com/wejs?wtype=cdsratingsonlywide&amp;uniq=439&amp;locationId=653107&amp;lang=en_US&amp;border=true&amp;shadow=true&amp;display_version=2"></script>\r\n'),
('L''Arene Bordeaux', 'Bordeaux', 15, 'Completely renovated in 2012, This XIX century Bordeaux bourgeois house combines the warmth of ancient stone houses and up to date comfort.<br />\r\nA patio offers opportunities to relax in summer, to drink a glass of Bordeaux wine while tasting “foie gras”, spannish ham or french cheese.<br />\r\nOn a wine tour or going south for holidays, in the city for business, just spending a couple of days, l’Arène will be the best break you can expect.', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d2828.7426050750346!2d-0.5856656843973447!3d44.847174979098476!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0xd5527e06703954b%3A0x252d764002b8adcb!2sMaison+d&#39;h%C3%B4tes+l&#39;Ar%C3%A8ne+de+Bordeaux!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1488279076089" frameborder="0" style="" allowfullscreen></iframe>', '<div id="TA_cdsratingsonlywide944" class="TA_cdsratingsonlywide">\r\n<ul id="piselO" class="TA_links 92S1Hvn">\r\n<li id="pIXgEL" class="ViGYRI8">\r\n<a target="_blank" href="https://www.tripadvisor.com/"><img src="https://www.tripadvisor.com/img/cdsi/img2/branding/tripadvisor_logo_transp_340x80-18034-2.png" alt="TripAdvisor"/></a>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<script src="https://www.jscache.com/wejs?wtype=cdsratingsonlywide&amp;uniq=944&amp;locationId=3297893&amp;lang=en_US&amp;border=true&amp;shadow=true&amp;display_version=2"></script>'),
('La Maison de Moliere', 'French Riviera', 12, 'Close to the Camargue and the Alpilles, located in the historical center of Arles, this large and elegant 18th century house is an invitation to leisure.\r\nWhether in the shade of its inner courtyard'' s arches, in its library / living room or en suite bedrooms with air conditionning, the house will offer you a well deserved harmony between cultural visits, leisure and life style.<br />\r\nThe rooms come appointed with high-end amenities such as Quagliotti, for linens, Annick Goutal with its Eau d''Hadrien and Oyuna for its cachemires, selected for their know-how and quality requirements.<br />\r\nYou can privatize the Maison Molière, with your family or friends and we can organize tailor-made programs for the duration of your stay.<br />\r\nThe atmosphere of La Maison Molière is one of leisure and calm and is therefore highly inadequate for children.', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m14!1m8!1m3!1d11542.785558835194!2d4.6239272!3d43.6752838!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x0%3A0x36e269d78ed44c4e!2sLa+Maison+Moli%C3%A8re!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1488279204363" frameborder="0" style="" allowfullscreen></iframe>', ''),
('La Suite Villa', 'Martinique', 13, 'Discover the French Antilles by staying at the Suite Villa, a five star hotel with suites, villas, restaurant and swimming pool. If you ‘ve been looking for a good spot among the Martinique Hotels and especially the luxury hotels, stop searching and visit our rooms and villas.<br />\r\nYou will see why guest choose La Suite Villa for their Martinique Holidays and why the travellers on Tripadvisor rank this hotel as one of the best hotels in Martinique.', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d3861.924780688105!2d-61.053701685070614!3d14.546293989837073!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x8c401de3d7080b45%3A0x362d618655d53f88!2sLa+Suite+Villa!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1490374205346" frameborder="0" style="" allowfullscreen></iframe>', '<div id="TA_cdsratingsonlywide33" class="TA_cdsratingsonlywide">\r\n<ul id="Q6mU4cV8" class="TA_links dwwqn54O">\r\n<li id="Zwo1ID" class="NFEohd9">\r\n<a target="_blank" href="https://www.tripadvisor.com/"><img src="https://www.tripadvisor.com/img/cdsi/img2/branding/tripadvisor_logo_transp_340x80-18034-2.png" alt="TripAdvisor"/></a>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<script src="https://www.jscache.com/wejs?wtype=cdsratingsonlywide&amp;uniq=33&amp;locationId=1637765&amp;lang=en_US&amp;border=true&amp;shadow=true&amp;display_version=2"></script>'),
('Le Clos Marcamps', 'Bordeaux', 10, 'In the heart of the vineyards of Bordeaux, half an hour from Bordeaux and Saint-Emilion, or also one hour and half from the Arcachon Bay, Clos Marcamps welcomes you in a chartreuse of the 19th century, entirely renovated with the charm and the comfort of today. This attractive guest house greets you such as a family home within its park, planted with hundred-year-old species where you will find quietness and serenity and where the children are pleased to find swing, swimming pool, rabbits, hens there…<br />\r\nThis charming property offers you 2 family suites and two classic rooms, all with terrace and independent entrance. They are decorated with charm and authenticity with a special care to the second-hand objects, which embellish the place. For your comfort this attractive guesthouse offers you cable television, Wi-Fi, kettle, Nespresso® machine and air conditioning in the rooms.', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d2819.4832332546753!2d-0.49987058466388323!3d45.035414869972875!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x480029a8393345ff%3A0xc27ac56ed0d07416!2sCLOS+MARCAMPS+-+H%C3%B4tel+de+charme+-+Ch%C3%A2teaux+et+H%C3%B4tels+Collection!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1490367556654" frameborder="0" style="" allowfullscreen></iframe>', '<div id="TA_cdsratingsonlywide341" class="TA_cdsratingsonlywide">\r\n<ul id="8t9WHxl" class="TA_links RKLqUe">\r\n<li id="rnc43lwYWzs" class="P9jdM2gnxrC3">\r\n<a target="_blank" href="https://www.tripadvisor.com/"><img src="https://www.tripadvisor.com/img/cdsi/img2/branding/tripadvisor_logo_transp_340x80-18034-2.png" alt="TripAdvisor"/></a>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<script src="https://www.jscache.com/wejs?wtype=cdsratingsonlywide&amp;uniq=341&amp;locationId=6373337&amp;lang=en_US&amp;border=true&amp;shadow=true&amp;display_version=2"></script>'),
('Les Aurochs', 'French Riviera', 15, 'At the heart of the Gulf of Saint- Tropez, this old sheepfold, out of sight and near the castle of grimaud, will seduce you with its tranquility.<br />\r\nThe guesthouse "The Aurochs " offers a real moment of authenticity, simplicity and sweetness.<br />\r\nLean back, the atmosphere and the welcoming hosts will make the rest!<br />\r\nHere, we enjoy life, we have a laugh around the swimming pool, we share a glass of rosé, a cocktail dinner, for a weekend or a week, with friends or family, you will feel delighted.<br />\r\nYour only regret: that you eventually must leave us.<br />\r\nOur five Holiday cottages and our 2 guest rooms with a refined decoration, have air conditioning for hot summer nights, a mini bar for a drink or to celebrate a magical moment.<br />\r\nIn the shade of palm trees, sun lovers can safely relax around the swimming pool.', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d2904.3160329048637!2d6.518357315553424!3d43.286702979135605!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x12cec9c48f9488af%3A0x3c1ec5ca6759e972!2sLES+AUROCHS!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1490349608513" frameborder="0" style="" allowfullscreen></iframe>', '<div id="TA_cdsratingsonlywide204" class="TA_cdsratingsonlywide">\r\n<ul id="G7rSxA24" class="TA_links DmSw6Ecv4So">\r\n<li id="SWMmjOX" class="AYF2uZeI">\r\n<a target="_blank" href="https://www.tripadvisor.com/"><img src="https://www.tripadvisor.com/img/cdsi/img2/branding/tripadvisor_logo_transp_340x80-18034-2.png" alt="TripAdvisor"/></a>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<script src="https://www.jscache.com/wejs?wtype=cdsratingsonlywide&amp;uniq=204&amp;locationId=4607584&amp;lang=en_US&amp;border=true&amp;shadow=true&amp;display_version=2"></script>'),
('Les Bruyères du Mont Saint-Michel', 'Normandie', 30, 'Our house is located 12 km from the Wonder of the West<br />\r\nThe old farmhouse is ideally located between St Malo and Granville. Ideal starting point to visit Normandy and Brittany. Less than 15 minutes away, Mont-St-Michel will impress you with its exceptional location in the heart of the Bay, where the powerful tides are among the fastest in the world.<br />\r\nCancale, Saint Malo, Granville, Fougères and Rennes are less than an hour''s drive away.<br />\r\nCalm and serenity in our guest rooms.<br />\r\nTo make the most of your stay in Les Bruyères du Mont, the large garden with trees and flowers, closed, welcomes you and offers you rest and relaxation.', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d1704979.1550291476!2d-2.868907643430964!3d48.51305860936419!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x480954acdede638b%3A0xc9cfe1bbc1613bf!2sChambres+d&#39;h%C3%B4tes+Les+Bruy%C3%A8res+du+Mont!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1490281615592"  frameborder="0" style="" allowfullscreen></iframe>', '<div id="TA_cdsratingsonlywide943" class="TA_cdsratingsonlywide">\r\n<ul id="kPPF4F" class="TA_links 3IGt0FdtlT5a">\r\n<li id="XcsxcM" class="QXsv9GU3T">\r\n<a target="_blank" href="https://www.tripadvisor.com/"><img src="https://www.tripadvisor.com/img/cdsi/img2/branding/tripadvisor_logo_transp_340x80-18034-2.png" alt="TripAdvisor"/></a>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<script src="https://www.jscache.com/wejs?wtype=cdsratingsonlywide&amp;uniq=943&amp;locationId=7395384&amp;lang=en_US&amp;border=true&amp;shadow=true&amp;display_version=2"></script>'),
('Les Chambres d''Annie', 'Deauville', 20, 'Located between sea and sky, a few minutes’ drive to Deauville and Honfleur, our guest bedroom benefit of an exceptional environment and an access to the sea in a few minutes in feet. In Annie’s room, every morning is a party.\r\nHanging from the sky, our guest home a side the sea. Soon as you arrive, you will bath or take a shower watching the sea, wearing silk bathrobes, warming the water for a tea….the rest of the story is yours !\r\nAnnie’s room, the luxury and elegance without ostentation.', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d2596.9703123135564!2d0.10685581575362652!3d49.390553579343205!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x47e02ceb0fd0af2d%3A0xd93a2fcae6b76341!2sLes+Chambres+d&#39;Annie!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1488279335184" frameborder="0" style="" allowfullscreen></iframe>', '<div id="TA_cdsratingsonlywide867" class="TA_cdsratingsonlywide">\r\n<ul id="CtyBW2TZrdy" class="TA_links rOggiA3xRxm">\r\n<li id="Pf3n8LJuycFY" class="gpTHha9Vq8Zg">\r\n<a target="_blank" href="https://www.tripadvisor.com/"><img src="https://www.tripadvisor.com/img/cdsi/img2/branding/tripadvisor_logo_transp_340x80-18034-2.png" alt="TripAdvisor"/></a>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<script src="https://www.jscache.com/wejs?wtype=cdsratingsonlywide&amp;uniq=867&amp;locationId=1739996&amp;lang=en_US&amp;border=true&amp;shadow=true&amp;display_version=2"></script>'),
('Les Loges du Théâtre', 'Lyon', 15, 'Les loges du Théâtre vous proposent 4 chambres doubles et une suite familiale au centre ville de Lyon avec parking privatif. Profitez toute l’année du spa extérieur & des autres prestations réservées aux hôtes.\r\nIdéal pour découvrir Lyon & la Croix Rousse ou pour vos déplacements professionnels, n’hésitez pas à réserver une chambre d’hôte digne d’un hôtel dans le centre-ville de Lyon !', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d2782.5922487722773!2d4.830822415632742!3d45.77936137910588!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x47f4eae1c2eb4d4b%3A0x18a21e1c61201afb!2sChambres+d&#39;h%C3%B4tes+Les+Loges+Du+Th%C3%A9%C3%A2tre!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1488381254973" frameborder="0" style="" allowfullscreen></iframe>', '<div id="TA_cdsratingsonlywide230" class="TA_cdsratingsonlywide">\r\n<ul id="rj73KjOt1gn" class="TA_links 5MpQcuKdApGs">\r\n<li id="BXOheS" class="IeLu0m">\r\n<a target="_blank" href="https://www.tripadvisor.com/"><img src="https://www.tripadvisor.com/img/cdsi/img2/branding/tripadvisor_logo_transp_340x80-18034-2.png" alt="TripAdvisor"/></a>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<script src="https://www.jscache.com/wejs?wtype=cdsratingsonlywide&amp;uniq=230&amp;locationId=4742057&amp;lang=en_US&amp;border=true&amp;shadow=true&amp;display_version=2"></script>'),
('Manoir de la Baronnie', 'Normandie', 12, 'Pour une courte escale, ou un séjour détente, le Manoir de La baronnie, vous ouvre ses chambres d''hôtes à St Malo, et vous accueille dans l’ambiance chaleureuse et authentique d’une grande maison de famille.<br />\r\nSituée à proximité immédiate des plages et du centre historique de St Malo, mais à l’écart de l’agitation touristique, le domaine vous propose ses chambres d’hôtes et gîtes  dans un cadre champêtre propice au repos et au ressourcement. Vous pourrez selon les saisons flâner dans le parc, bronzer au bord de la piscine, ou vous détendre dans le grand salon devant une bonne flambée.<br />\r\nPour une remise en forme sportive ou une relaxation en toute tranquillité, vous pourrez également profiter de notre spa en espace privatif.\r\nPour une expérience insolite, vous pourrez également passer la nuit dans une charmante petite roulotte Tzigane.', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d2637.316659838817!2d-1.9992817842726076!3d48.62292217926509!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x480e8154c427267b%3A0xa71c62b9c9b1edc8!2sManoir+de+la+Baronnie!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1488376627310" frameborder="0" style="" allowfullscreen></iframe>', '<div id="TA_cdsratingsonlywide628" class="TA_cdsratingsonlywide">\r\n<ul id="7aujW0ON" class="TA_links 3tG7nPettO">\r\n<li id="9ncZhEfJG7r" class="zw06m5">\r\n<a target="_blank" href="https://www.tripadvisor.com/"><img src="https://www.tripadvisor.com/img/cdsi/img2/branding/tripadvisor_logo_transp_340x80-18034-2.png" alt="TripAdvisor"/></a>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<script src="https://www.jscache.com/wejs?wtype=cdsratingsonlywide&amp;uniq=628&amp;locationId=2018543&amp;lang=en_US&amp;border=true&amp;shadow=true&amp;display_version=2"></script>'),
('My Home For You', 'Paris', 20, 'Envie de séjourner autrement à Paris ?\r\nChoisissez une maison d’hôtes urbaine où tout est réuni pour que vous vous sentiez chez vous. Votre hôte, Jean Étienne, vous accueille chaleureusement ! Son expérience professionnelle dans le tourisme parisien et dans l’hôtellerie de luxe lui ont donné l’envie d’imaginer ce nouveau lieu. Aujourd’hui, il vous invite à découvrir une adresse idéale pour vivre et découvrir différemment Paris.<br />\r\nMy Home For You est situé dans un bel immeuble édifié en 1875 au 10, Boulevard Poissonnière, dans le 9ème arrondissement, en plein cœur de Paris, face au cinéma Le Grand Rex.<br />\r\n4 chambres d''hôtes a été créées en 2015 dans un appartement entièrement rénové. Nous avons apporté un soin tout particulier au confort et à la décoration de chaque pièce, de chaque chambre. Meubles de famille ou chinés à Drouot ou chez les antiquaires, tableaux et gravures du 19e siècle, reproductions authentiques d’icônes du design. <br />\r\nChaque chambre vous plonge dans une atmosphère parisienne unique, inspirée par les quartiers parisiens (Palais Royal, Grands Boulevards, Trocadéro) ou encore par le Musée National des Arts Asiatiques - Guimet.', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d2624.3245265696114!2d2.3447570157358455!3d48.87108967928882!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x47e66e160b05be8b%3A0x4e2438c944ed6dd1!2sChambres+d&#39;h%C3%B4tes-B%26B+Paris+%22My+Home+For+You%22!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1490195685904" frameborder="0" style="" allowfullscreen></iframe>', '<div id="TA_cdsratingsonlywide54" class="TA_cdsratingsonlywide">\r\n<ul id="R3E5yO8ukcOL" class="TA_links q4ZOOc1Yo8IE">\r\n<li id="JUFjpt8L1UQ1" class="008nVJ5">\r\n<a target="_blank" href="https://www.tripadvisor.com/"><img src="https://www.tripadvisor.com/img/cdsi/img2/branding/tripadvisor_logo_transp_340x80-18034-2.png" alt="TripAdvisor"/></a>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<script src="https://www.jscache.com/wejs?wtype=cdsratingsonlywide&amp;uniq=54&amp;locationId=10062820&amp;lang=en_US&amp;border=true&amp;shadow=true&amp;display_version=2"></script>\r\n'),
('Villa Arguibel', 'Biarritz', 15, 'Maison d’hôtes de luxe :<br />\r\nArguibel à Guethary, près de Biarritz, allie luxe et design dans un concept qui se situe entre hôtel quatre étoiles et maison d''hôtes de prestige. Boutique hôtel ou chambre d''hôte de charme au bord de l''océan, vue sur mer ou sur montagnes du Pays Basque.<br />\r\nLa villa Arguibel propose cinq chambres dont deux suites, toutes au décor singulier qui marie avec harmonie meubles anciens revisités et design, peintures contemporaines et sculptures d''art, bois flotté pour le côté mer et peaux de bêtes pour le côté nature.<br />\r\nOn profitera de ses terrasses pour savourer les délicieux petits déjeuners et se reposer devant un décor magistral emprunt de sérénité, les montagnes et l''horizon en ligne de mire.<br />\r\nArguibel, ce n''est pas seulement une chambre d''hôte, mais c''est aussi de larges parties communes entièrement dédiées aux hôtes, son salon vous accueillera pour écouter de la musique ou discuter entre amis, sa bibliothèque et son bar privé à vins et champagnes vous attendront à l'' heure de vos envies, enfin son salon de lecture vous invitera à la détente. <br />\r\nLa villa Arguibel, entre Biarritz et St Jean de Luz, se situe à un kilomètre de l''océan et des plages Guéthary.<br />\r\nÉquipements les plus appréciés : Parking gratuit, Connexion Wi-Fi gratuite, Chambres non-fumeurs.\r\n', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d3101923.2999439165!2d-4.832418311786236!3d42.47058806677543!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0xd5113f56719a647%3A0x64b72f698b758721!2sArguibel!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1490283579721" frameborder="0" style="" allowfullscreen></iframe>', '<div id="TA_cdsratingsonlywide381" class="TA_cdsratingsonlywide">\r\n<ul id="4YmE7gCBd" class="TA_links OgPA3HvCi2Sw">\r\n<li id="IYCsb13R" class="ySnWJzZmF">\r\n<a target="_blank" href="https://www.tripadvisor.com/"><img src="https://www.tripadvisor.com/img/cdsi/img2/branding/tripadvisor_logo_transp_340x80-18034-2.png" alt="TripAdvisor"/></a>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<script src="https://www.jscache.com/wejs?wtype=cdsratingsonlywide&amp;uniq=381&amp;locationId=1566677&amp;lang=en_US&amp;border=true&amp;shadow=true&amp;display_version=2"></script>'),
('Villa Belza', 'Reunion Island', 20, 'La villa Belza est un havre de paix où l''on se sent dans un univers de zénitude dès la traversée du portail.<br />\r\nLa décoration est faite avec goût et elle amène au repos et à la détente.<br />\r\nLa villa est magnifique, les chambres décorées avec goût et le jardin est resplendissant avec gros plus pour le jacuzzi!<br />\r\nNous vous accueillons dans un décor exotique où  se mêlent chaleur, et détente. Venez découvrir des saveurs tropicales à travers la gastronomie créole.<br />\r\nVous ne serez pas déçus à la Villa Belza.', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d3716.604831219423!2d55.49534771502404!3d-21.32662548583774!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x21780a73fc7fd413%3A0xec64592fa70c232f!2sVilla+Belza!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1490262996586" frameborder="0" style="" allowfullscreen></iframe>', '<div id="TA_cdsratingsonlywide796" class="TA_cdsratingsonlywide">\r\n<ul id="m09V2P0z1w" class="TA_links RBd1M7i">\r\n<li id="GO9szUeOn1PH" class="v5FF1RGPmRCW">\r\n<a target="_blank" href="https://www.tripadvisor.com/"><img src="https://www.tripadvisor.com/img/cdsi/img2/branding/tripadvisor_logo_transp_340x80-18034-2.png" alt="TripAdvisor"/></a>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<script src="https://www.jscache.com/wejs?wtype=cdsratingsonlywide&amp;uniq=796&amp;locationId=10093073&amp;lang=en_US&amp;border=true&amp;shadow=true&amp;display_version=2"></script>'),
('Villa du Square', 'Paris', 25, 'Private hotel, built in the years 20, which is in an upper class of 16th arrondissement in Paris.<br />\r\nAs Soon as you arrive, you will emerge in an original atmosphere, where contrast modern architectural and classicism of the house.<br />\r\nAt your convenience, you will find five comfortable bedrooms disposed for your optimum comfort.<br />\r\nA driver will be available to you for your visits, he will take you to the airport but also in touristic sites close to Paris.<br />\r\nIf you would like to rest, we will reserve relaxing sessions with a sport coach of the villa, Spa or Hamman sessions, or even swimming in the famous pool Molitor.<br />\r\nFor the cultural trendy, we will offer you cultural customize visit, to discover the story of Paris.<br />\r\nDo not wait any longer to make you happy; come enjoy fun moment in the 16th, upper class arrondissement of Paris.', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d2625.3336109401093!2d2.262618215735212!3d48.85184847928693!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x47e67ab1e5b6862f%3A0xc893dea8d083c8a5!2sVilla+Du+Square!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1488279376977" frameborder="0" style="" allowfullscreen></iframe>', '<div id="TA_cdsratingsonlywide812" class="TA_cdsratingsonlywide">\r\n<ul id="bg0WOM2eE" class="TA_links Cwu7HoLb3">\r\n<li id="R5VBJ2yL2t" class="bOMQe4Yl">\r\n<a target="_blank" href="https://www.tripadvisor.com/"><img src="https://www.tripadvisor.com/img/cdsi/img2/branding/tripadvisor_logo_transp_340x80-18034-2.png" alt="TripAdvisor"/></a>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<script src="https://www.jscache.com/wejs?wtype=cdsratingsonlywide&amp;uniq=812&amp;locationId=8117151&amp;lang=en_US&amp;border=true&amp;shadow=true&amp;display_version=2"></script>'),
('Villa Goeland', 'Biarritz', 15, 'Built in the XVIII century, the villa Montebello will become the villa Ravize and will get the latest architectural changes between the 1900 and 1903 and finally become the villa Goëland.<br />\r\nThis familial Place and its four guest bedrooms, with organise architectural is unbelievably placed at 50 meters from the most beautiful beaches of Biarritz.\r\nThe day will start with a breakfast and the masters of the house having jolly conversation.<br />\r\nYou can notice at proximity 3 beaches, many golf courses, the casino, the thalassotherapy and horse ride, a large choices of restaurants accessible walking (from the tapas bar to the various food) or even shopping, museum visits, to discover Basque culture and walks are waiting for you and will also allow you to spend memorable moments.<br />\r\nYou will take advantage of the big Livingroom with chimenea and panoramic terrace, giving you optimum view at 180° from Spain to the South coast Landaise to the North, going through the Pays Basque.', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d2894.945383051869!2d-1.5684959844404742!3d43.482610179127505!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0xd516b257f8300ad%3A0x9663e1cac8c29ec6!2sVilla+le+Go%C3%A9land!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1488279454147" frameborder="0" style="" allowfullscreen></iframe>', '<div id="TA_cdsratingsonlywide842" class="TA_cdsratingsonlywide">\r\n<ul id="AgCqN3eZB" class="TA_links xGFDK7Vewl0">\r\n<li id="z8cLBcnO6qs" class="I4hbno5dmeCi">\r\n<a target="_blank" href="https://www.tripadvisor.com/"><img src="https://www.tripadvisor.com/img/cdsi/img2/branding/tripadvisor_logo_transp_340x80-18034-2.png" alt="TripAdvisor"/></a>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<script src="https://www.jscache.com/wejs?wtype=cdsratingsonlywide&amp;uniq=842&amp;locationId=312448&amp;lang=en_US&amp;border=true&amp;shadow=true&amp;display_version=2"></script>'),
('Villa Laurina', 'Reunion Island', 25, 'Un peu de magie solaire  :chaque soir le soleil se noit dans la baie de St Paul... A déguster sur notre terrasse. En fonction de la saison, il varie son point d’impact. Chaque soir, le ciel s’embrase et rougeoit. Vu de cette altitude, c’est un spectacle mémorable.<br />\r\nLa villa dispose d’un Gazebo d’où vous pourrez profiter confortablement du spectacle.<br />\r\nUn peu de romantisme : célébrez un mariage à la Villa Laurina est un privilège dont vos hôtes se souviendront longtemps. L’atmosphère particulière du lieu, le calme et un panorama grandiose concourent à vous procurer un réel sentiment de bonheur. Notre villa est un nid, une base d’envol pour les amoureux au sein d’un parc arboré de 2 hectares.<br />\r\nUn peu de frisson : si la tentation de l’aventure vous guette, sachez qu’une base de parapente est présente à 500m et que depuis le Maïdo, les randonnées sont possibles vers Mafate.', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d3724.059203749864!2d55.31753431501932!3d-21.03031698599747!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x2182857ca7cc0ba3%3A0xe7d2c2bbe9dbea1f!2sVilla+Laurina!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1490369940401" frameborder="0" style="" allowfullscreen></iframe>', '<div id="TA_cdsratingsonlywide954" class="TA_cdsratingsonlywide">\r\n<ul id="WNTkyP5" class="TA_links OlxeYc8448ew">\r\n<li id="K7sb9qvHsHfP" class="7WGtQGuCt">\r\n<a target="_blank" href="https://www.tripadvisor.com/"><img src="https://www.tripadvisor.com/img/cdsi/img2/branding/tripadvisor_logo_transp_340x80-18034-2.png" alt="TripAdvisor"/></a>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<script src="https://www.jscache.com/wejs?wtype=cdsratingsonlywide&amp;uniq=954&amp;locationId=9468380&amp;lang=en_US&amp;border=true&amp;shadow=true&amp;display_version=2"></script>'),
('Villa Montabord', 'Paris', 100, 'In the heart of Paris, close to Batignolles and at the foot of Montmartre, the villa Montabord is in a ravishing private area “La Cité des Fleurs”.\r\nWe will welcome you in the heart of our guesthouse for your stay in the French capital, where you will find four luxurious bedrooms, where architectural, ancient furniture’s will mix to offer you the ideal comfort and a unique peaceful mood \r\n\r\nCome move around on foot or with a bike in the charming neighbourhood of Montmartre, or in the plain of Monceau. Do not hesitate to take public transportation to discover the most touristic sites of Paris.\r\n\r\nLet’s discover the secrets of Paris, and make your journey a memorable moment in the Villa of Montabord.', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d2623.250186216353!2d2.317217315736535!3d48.89156897929075!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x47e66fac024ea99d%3A0xcb690ad92df0a041!2sChambres+d&#39;h%C3%B4tes+B%26B+Paris+Villa+Montabord!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1488278513586" frameborder="0" style="" allowfullscreen></iframe>', '<div id="TA_cdsratingsonlywide821" class="TA_cdsratingsonlywide">\r\n<ul id="bhqgOU92T04a" class="TA_links C2rL4J">\r\n<li id="7OzDNl6On" class="4vnJiXIimtjd">\r\n<a target="_blank" href="https://www.tripadvisor.fr/"><img src="https://www.tripadvisor.fr/img/cdsi/img2/branding/tripadvisor_logo_transp_340x80-18034-2.png" alt="TripAdvisor"/></a>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<script src="https://www.jscache.com/wejs?wtype=cdsratingsonlywide&amp;uniq=821&amp;locationId=7906143&amp;lang=eng_US&amp;border=true&amp;shadow=true&amp;display_version=2"></script>');
INSERT INTO `ville` (`ville`, `description_ville`, `id`) VALUES
('Biarritz', 'Costal city, Biarritz is universally known for its Thalassotherapy, appeared in the years of 1970.\r\nFrom its many activities, Biarritz is the ideal place for a family vacation or to enjoy swimming activities: surfing, long beach walk with the scenographer lightening of the Eiffel tour. Pierre Bideau, is famous for being the best surf spot.\r\nFor the sportive ones, Biarritz is recognized as the historical capital in the Europeans continent.\r\nBiarritz also rime with golf. The amateur of golf will have many choices from 10 golfs in a 50-km square.\r\nIt’s really a city with diverse activities to make everyone happy, from the youngest to the oldest.', 'Biarritz'),
('Deauville', 'The city of elegant entertainment and good taste can receive, where everyone can find his happiness. \r\nInescapable short stop of boaters, the seaside resort internationally famous know how to charm his visitors with class, between the guests, his casino and sea swim establishment.\r\nThe 653 meters of woods the walk offer an astonish view, sun light with clouds, and the reflexion of the water, lay in a colourful site. Transat and beach cabin are the necessary accessories to admire this beautiful board which take a new dimension during the American movie festival. With the rich program of the international centre, the small city can brag about being a cultural pole in first plan.\r\nThe image of Deauville, is of course the horse ride, the race, that attract the passionate and the profanes.', 'Deauville'),
('Bordeaux', 'Come visit the city of wine, capital of the biggest winery of, France, very well known for his wine, trademark.\r\nYou will reside in a cosmopolitan city, where the wine and gastronomy go together.\r\nThe identity of Bordeaux, you will find it in its important prints in the wine making.\r\nEither you are a wine lover like the Sauternes, Saint Emilion, or Chateaux Margaux, or you would like to amaze your senses or your taste buzz, our homes in Bordeaux will delight you with wine tasting around the finest ones.', 'Bordeaux'),
('Strasbourg', 'Located in the eastern of France, and being among the patrimony heritage worldwide, Strasbourg is considered in France as being the Christmas capital because of its exceptional Christmas market, which it’s been famous for 445 years.\r\nWith New York and Geneva, Strasbourg is one of the city which welcome the international institutions without being the state capital.\r\nYou will also discover a rich gastronomy invented since 1780.\r\nCome enjoy choucoutre, flambé or the famous foie gras in convivial taverns, where you will find fine Alsatians beers created since 1268.\r\nEither you into castle, bike riding, good restaurant: you can do it all.\r\nStrasbourg deserve your visit.', 'Strasbourg'),
('Paris', 'Capital of France, Paris is not only known to be the prettiest city in the world. Paris is also a mix of harmonious art, fashion, literature and gastronomy.\r\nA cultural exceptional harmony with a rich historical stamp and ancient architectural, built in huge edifice like the famous Eiffel tour or the cathedral Notre dame de Paris*\r\nBreathing fresh essence or walking in the street of Paris, savouring French baguette or croissant for breakfast, admiring the architectural beauty, discovering a new mentality and meeting Parisians will make your escapade memorable.\r\nParis will transfer you its positive energy.', 'Paris'),
('Haute-Savoie', 'Made of Lake Annecy, and Leman, the Haute-Savoie is a French Region, amazingly known for its fresh mountain air and it skiing stations. The Haute-Savoie will ravish you in summer or winter because of its huge massif like the Mont Blanc.\r\nIt’s a famous department for its winter sports and for the amateurs of summer hiking.\r\nYou will delight the savours traditional locales like “The fondue” or “The raclette”, in a warm place, next to the fire, in your chalet.\r\nYou will discover the Savoyards products made local from French territory.', 'Haute_Savoie'),
('French Riviera', 'In 1923, two young rich Americans, Gerald and Sara Murphy discovered the beauty of the city Antibes, unknown at the time, they convinced the boss of the Cap Hotel to remain open on summer, while most of the notable were coming in winter. \r\nThe Murphy invited many of their notable’s friends such as Pablo Picasso or Hernest Hemingway who made that region appreciated, and it became the place where everybody wanted to be seen.\r\nThat is how the appellation “French-Riviera” was born, the English appellation is “Cote d’ Azur” which represent the oriental part of the littoral Mediterranean including Monaco.\r\nThroughout your visit, we will show you a magnify part of France, to move, discover Saint Tropez, Cannes, travel the path of the littoral looking for a nice creek.\r\nBut also, the “Cote d’Azur”, its inside Collins is full of well-preserved zone.\r\nThe “French Riviera «is beautiful small villages unknow to the big public, it’s a must discover, mostly for it amazing beautiful blue sky.\r\nSpend your vacation in Cote d’Azur, is giving yourself beautiful and amazing natural sites to see.', 'French_Riviera'),
('Reunion Island', 'Located in the archipelago of Mascarenes, the Reunion island, offer to the travellers a total escape in a tropical island of the Indian ocean. On the influential crossroad of Africa, Asia, and Europe, the Reunion is a land of mix cultures.\r\nAt the Reunion island, swim in the Grand Bleu, it is leaving a magical meeting with the whales and the dolphins, it is witnessing the sunset on the ocean, it is jumping to discover the wealth of the fauna and the flora underwater, an astonishing moonlight set, a ground of hard floor, land covered in orange, brown stones are waiting for you.  \r\nThe Reunion is a land of contrast images, landscape, populations, cooking’s, and religions. Its traditions show a unique history of the Reunion.\r\nIf you like to discover heaven on earth, do not hesitate and fly for the Reunion.', 'Reunion_Island'),
('French Polynesia', 'Located in the heart of the Pacific Ocean, the French Polynesia, lay on a maritime space of 4 million per KM², a surface like Europe.\r\nThe French Polynesia enchanted generations of explorer, writers, travellers, painters.\r\nThe magnify decors is there to comfort the image of Eden found. The high island rise majestically on top of the opal lagoons.\r\nBetween the parties and festivals, the mythology and the beliefs, the archeologic discovery and historical, the Polynesian art, the dance and the choreography, and the tattoos, they is something to please anybody.\r\nDiscover the local specialities, enjoy yourself on traditional rhythms at the beach with spectacular choreographies.\r\nLet yourself transported in beautiful places and leave to discover famous islands like Tahiti, Bora Bora for a great time.\r\nThe Polynesia is only waiting for you! ', 'French_Polynesia'),
('Corse', 'Commonly called « beauty island » for her natural unique patrimony and her sunny weather.\r\nHeavenly looking beaches at the interior of most hidden villages. Corse is a beautiful island with many secrets and savage force. It’s an island with astonish places in summer, enjoy the walk and many nautical activities and during the long winter soak in the deep Corse, discover the making of local products and appreciate the Corse wine while learning the language spoken there, Italian.\r\nCorse will seduce you for a memorable escapade.', 'Corse'),
('Lyon', 'The wealth of Lyon come from his big variety of architectural styles, from Gallo-Roman to modern years.\r\nNext to Beaujolais, Alpes and the Massif Central and the Provence, Lyon is perfect to make discovery in the central of France.\r\nFestival, concert, there is always something going on in this city that exist for 2000 years.\r\nAfter Paris, Lyon is the first gay friendly city of France.\r\nNature, gastronomy and landscape go very well with this city, that you can visit with your friends and family.', 'Lyon'),
('Martinique', 'MartiniqueIn the heart of the Caribbean archipelago, Martinique is a part of the "Lesser Antilles" also known as the "Island in the wind". Its shores are bathed by the Caribbean Sea in the West and by the Atlantic Ocean in the East. Its closest neighbours are: Saint Lucia (situated in 40 kilometres) to the south and Dominica (situated in 25 kilometres) to the north, close enough for you to see them in good weather. The Martinique offers a mild climate of the "eternal summer", with an average annual temperature of 26 ° C. You can relax on a beach, go for walks, discover the Martinique culture, or even do some water activities, for the most courageous. Let yourself be carried away by this exotic atmosphere, Caribbean gastronomy and the festive atmosphere that reigns on the Island throughout the year. Martinique is waiting for you!!', 'Martinique'),
('Arles', 'Un patrimoine romain et roman, ville de van Gogh, Capitale de la Camargue et chaque année le rendez vous de la photographie, de la musique, de la tauromachie... \r\nArles est une ville d’art et d’histoire, classée par l’UNESCO comme Patrimoine mondial de l’Humanité à triple titre : \r\n- pour son centre ancien et l’ensemble de ses monuments romains et romans, \r\n- en tant que Chemin de St Jacques de Compostelle (également Chemin de Rome et de Jérusalem). Le Chemin d’Arles est depuis le Moyen Age l’une des quatre voies traversant la France et l’Europe vers St Jacques, \r\n- en tant qu’espace naturel d’intérêt mondial : inscription de la Camargue au réseau mondial des Réserves biosphères.', 'Arles'),
('Saint-Barthelemy', 'Between the natural luxury and the art of living, chosen by many celebrities in the world, Saint Barthelemy impose itself as the French Antilles island of the moment. This small island was named “Bartolomeo” from the name of Christopher Columbus brother. Originally from a population who are very attached to their traditions, you will meet extraordinary people who will welcome you warm fully.<br />\r\nAccordion, Tambourine, maracas, and neighbourhood party, fun rhythm and the joy of life of his habitants.<br />\r\nYou will land in a luxurious island, in an idyllic property where you will savour local. You will also discover artisanal work, also the work of wheat straw use to make hats.<br />\r\nEither you would like to get married or just to spend heavenly vacation, St Barthelemy is waiting for you.', 'saint-barthelemy'),
('Reims', 'A Reims, l’histoire s’étend sur plus de 2000 ans. Vous n''imaginez pas ce qui vous attend !\nDe l’époque gallo-romaine à maintenant, Reims a joué un rôle central dans l’Histoire. Pour en avoir le cœur net, il suffit d’observer le patrimoine de la ville.\nReims, capitale romaine, Reims, cité des sacres des rois de France, Reims, ville martyre de la Première Guerre Mondiale, Reims, laboratoire architectural, Reims, symbole de paix et de réconciliation... Autant d’expressions pour désigner une ville aux multiples facettes, capitale du Nord de l’Empire Romain, siège du baptême de Clovis et des sacres royaux, bombardée et détruite à 80% pendant la GRANDE GUERRE , reconstruite dans les années 20-30 dans le style ART-DÉCO , siège du quartier général d’Eisenhower, où l’Allemagne nazie a signé sa capitulation le 7 mai 1945, puis où en 1962 a été célébrée la réconciliation entre la France et l’Allemagne. Les 3 sites classés au  PATRIMOINE MONDIAL DE L''UNESCO , les  MONUMENTS  et  MUSÉES  de la ville et de ses alentours témoignent de ce passé historique.\n\nCoronation City, Champagne town... Reims iseager to show you the legacy of itsgloriouspast and to lead youinto a prestigiousrealm of the mostcelebrated and festive of wines.\nReims, an Art and History City, opens up to youwithitsthree UNESCO World Heritage sites whichshould not bemissed.\nStrollthrough the streets of Reims, by day or by night : many sites, monuments and museums show the history of Reims, from the Gallo-Roman to the modern era, goingthrough the Art Decoperiod.\n', 'Reims'),
('Normandie', 'The Normandy is known as a haven of peace. Between the sea and the country, it offers you a multitude of magnificent sceneries. With its rich history, Normandy is highly appreciated by tourists, due to its famous sea resorts, its nature and local products.\nIts 600 km long cost, offers a view on its majestic cliffs, its marvellous sand beaches, it famous sea resorts, such as Deauville, Dieppe, Cabourg, Le Touquet, Etretat, Fécamp, Trouville, Honfleur. The region itself is rich in history and has much more to share: the numerous Abbayes (Mont Saint Michel), the castles, the ruins, the Bayeux tapestry, military cemeteries, monuments and legendary disembarkation beaches.\nLes Hautes d’Etretat is a lovely place, locatedat a few metersfrom the famous Etretat city. Known for itscliffs and pebblebeaches, place of inspiration for manyrenownedartists, this place isperfect if youwish to change thescenery.\n\nThis charming mansion willofferyouhigh class services whilemainteningitsgenuine soul. Come and enjoy the soothingatmosphereofourrooms all having a terrace and ourgardenthatwillmakeyoudiscover the French « Art de Vivre ».\nwith a gardenview.\n\nNo matter the seasonyouwillbeseduced by Les Hauts d’Etretat !\n', 'Normandie'),
('Saint Barth', '', 'Saint-barth'),
('Marseille', 'Marseille, also known as "the gate to the world", is the oldest city in France – built around its important commercial port. Founded in 600 BC by Greek sailors of Phocaea, Marseille is the first port of France. It is also the main quarters of an archbishop, the city of university and the capital of the departments Bouches-du-Rhone. The city owes its expansion and prosperity to its port, which is an important trans-shipment point with goods destined for North Africa and Asia, especially the petol that occupies an eminent position.', 'Marseille');
